Build-time vs.¬†run-time

Put this code, temporarily, into columns.R:

build_time <- Sys.time()

run_time <- function() {
  Sys.time()
}


devtools::load_all()
try build_time, run_time()




If you need to delay evaluation, try a function.

Curly-curly: {{}}

glue lets you interpolate strings:
greet <- function(name) {
  glue::glue("Hello {name}")
}
greet("there")

Tidy eval lets you interpolate arguments:
mutate_greet <- function(.data, greeting) {
  .data |>
    dplyr::mutate(greeting = {{ greeting }})
}
